{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Place tomatoes in a roasting dish, then drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with sugar and thyme leaves. Roast for 20 minutes (170°C). Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Place butter, shallots, leeks, bacon (if using) and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add Arbroath Smokie or smoked haddock, roasted tomatoes together with juices, tomato purée, stock, lemon juice, balsamic vinegar, paprika, salt and pepper then cook <nobr>12 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Blend <nobr>2 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add cream and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Taste and add extra seasoning if needed before serving hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["800 g fresh tomatoes, halved","50 g olive oil","1 tsp sugar","2 tsp fresh thyme leaves","30 g butter","50 g shallots","50 g leeks, white part, cut in pieces","50 g unsmoked bacon, cut in pieces (optional)","2 garlic cloves","150 g Arbroath smokie, bones and skin removed, cut in pieces (3 cm)","20 g tomato purée","500 g fish stock","25 g lemon juice","1 tsp balsamic vinegar","½ tsp smoked paprika","1 tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, or to taste","140 g double cream"]}],"id":"r92979","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-OnKFhyFr_bo\/XZMyaJNUL1I\/AAAAAAAAakg\/uzn0T0M43NU1EjLZgrt_jboKYAbdhIdjQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CDpOLL_lf9q2Fctn.png","title":"Arbroath Smokie Soup","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.6 g","fat":"24.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"8.2 g","calories":"1193 kJ \/ 285 kcal"},"usefulItems":"roasting dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This delicately flavoured soup would be equally at home on the table of a fine restaurant, as a starter at a dinner party, or as a lunch served with crusty bread. You can substitute smoked mackerel or kippers for the Arbroath Smokie if you wish - all are oily fish which are rich in vitamins A and D and omega-3 fatty acids.","Serves 6 for lunch or 8 as a starter."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","6 portions"]}